01:27.468 --> 01:30.538
Just thought that we should be ready

01:30.539 --> 01:32.739
<i>in case it isn't benign,</i>

01:32.740 --> 01:33.875
because then the

01:33.876 --> 01:36.077
operation could potentially be...

01:36.078 --> 01:37.879
Fatal.

01:38.046 --> 01:40.848
I think we should try and remain positive.

01:42.885 --> 01:44.152
It's all over.

01:44.153 --> 01:45.553
What's the point in being miserable?

01:45.554 --> 01:47.021
We don't know what's gonna happen.

01:47.022 --> 01:49.691
You're going to die.

01:50.058 --> 01:52.361
Listen, darling.

01:52.760 --> 01:55.696
If that does happen then,

01:56.097 --> 01:57.899
I am ready.

01:59.066 --> 02:00.233
You're so young.

02:00.234 --> 02:02.904
I've got everything I could
possibly ever have wanted.

02:02.905 --> 02:04.771
I've got a wonderful husband

02:04.772 --> 02:05.807
<i>who loves me,</i>

02:05.808 --> 02:07.774
<i>I've got two great kids,</i>

02:07.775 --> 02:08.574
and I'm an architect,

02:08.576 --> 02:10.511
which is what I always dreamed of.

02:10.512 --> 02:13.114
There's not a single thing in
my life that I would change,

02:13.115 --> 02:15.549
and there aren't many
people who could say that.

02:15.550 --> 02:18.219
You really wouldn't change anything?

02:18.854 --> 02:21.523
Not even moving to Canada?

02:25.193 --> 02:27.527
Look, if I do really
only have five days left,

02:27.528 --> 02:30.198
I want everything to remain normal

02:30.199 --> 02:31.666
so I can enjoy my life

02:31.667 --> 02:33.668
<i>exactly as it is.</i>

02:33.669 --> 02:35.836
Yeah, that makes sense.

02:35.837 --> 02:37.738
Oh yeah, and the
doctor said to avoid

02:37.739 --> 02:39.573
<i>any unnecessary stress,</i>

02:39.574 --> 02:41.241
<i>so please don't tell anyone,</i>

02:41.242 --> 02:42.710
<i>and that actually includes Kaitlyn.</i>

02:42.711 --> 02:43.978
Kaitlyn, hi, yeah.

02:43.979 --> 02:45.947
<i>Your mother has a brain tumour,</i>

02:45.948 --> 02:47.749
<i>she's gonna die.</i>

02:48.683 --> 02:50.485
Yeah.

02:51.552 --> 02:52.986
Yeah.

02:52.987 --> 02:55.690
And she doesn't want anyone to know.

02:55.691 --> 02:59.494
So if you could keep it to yourself.

02:59.760 --> 03:00.961
<i>Yeah.</i>

03:19.514 --> 03:20.715
Grace.

03:20.716 --> 03:21.716
What did the doctor say?

03:21.717 --> 03:22.849
He said I'm fine.

03:22.850 --> 03:24.018
But you blacked out,

03:24.019 --> 03:25.085
<i>it had to be something serious.</i>

03:25.086 --> 03:26.721
He said low blood pressure
and to drink more water,

03:26.722 --> 03:27.788
but I'm fine.

03:27.789 --> 03:29.590
I'll let everyone know.
We've all been so worried.

03:29.591 --> 03:30.924
<i>Absolutely nothing to worry about.</i>

03:30.925 --> 03:32.926
Grace. Are you okay?

03:32.927 --> 03:35.662
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Absolutely fine, thank you.

03:35.663 --> 03:37.465
Hi, Grace.

03:50.878 --> 03:51.878
Hey.

03:51.879 --> 03:52.913
Hi.

03:52.914 --> 03:54.549
Just low blood pressure, huh?

03:54.550 --> 03:55.816
Yeah, yeah.

03:55.817 --> 03:57.050
<i>Hey, you know the Millwood Project?</i>

03:57.051 --> 03:58.619
Yes.

03:58.620 --> 03:59.853
<i>Is there any chance
that the gang could get</i>

03:59.854 --> 04:02.556
