- Okay.

04:43.197 --> 04:44.999
It's after eight.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.667
Yeah, just-just tidying up

04:47.668 --> 04:48.869
<i>a few loose ends.</i>

04:48.870 --> 04:50.939
Goodnight, Ben.

04:51.139 --> 04:52.941
Night.

04:59.281 --> 05:00.948
She went to work?

05:00.949 --> 05:02.950
Yeah, and look at the time.

05:02.951 --> 05:05.119
Who works overtime when you're dying?

05:05.120 --> 05:06.854
Shouldn't she be out

05:06.855 --> 05:08.688
making her last wishes come true?

05:08.689 --> 05:09.857
No, she's-no she's got that,

05:09.858 --> 05:12.092
what's that word that she
always says about me because

05:12.093 --> 05:13.861
I passed out at that party and

05:13.862 --> 05:16.830
<i>she said I was drunk
and I was just sleeping?</i>

05:16.831 --> 05:18.667
Alcoholism?

05:19.701 --> 05:20.700
Last straw.

05:20.701 --> 05:21.736
That's two words.

05:21.737 --> 05:22.736
Denial.

05:22.737 --> 05:23.837
Denial, yes, yes.

05:23.838 --> 05:26.006
Denial, she's in denial.

05:26.007 --> 05:28.842
But maybe you're overreacting.

05:28.843 --> 05:30.311
<i>You said yourself</i>

05:30.312 --> 05:31.912
<i>if they find out that the
brain tumour is benign</i>

05:31.913 --> 05:34.314
when they do the surgery on Monday,

05:34.315 --> 05:35.849
they may be able to cut it out,

05:35.850 --> 05:39.521
<i>do a little radiation
if necessary and</i>

05:40.021 --> 05:40.888
she could be fine.

05:40.889 --> 05:43.691
Doctor said he wanted her to be ready.

05:44.925 --> 05:46.727
Fuck.

05:49.865 --> 05:51.665
I don't think I can do this.

05:51.666 --> 05:53.133
I'm feeling dizzy all the time and I-

05:53.134 --> 05:54.268
I can't find a pulse.

05:54.269 --> 05:57.905
Dad, this isn't about us.

05:57.906 --> 06:00.340
You know, it's kind of
about us, too, isn't it?

06:00.341 --> 06:02.143
We have to help her.

06:02.144 --> 06:03.410
Help her what?

06:03.411 --> 06:04.778
Help her be ready.

06:04.779 --> 06:07.449
Well, she-she says she is ready.

06:07.949 --> 06:08.948
You're living your life,

06:08.949 --> 06:11.318
and then someone says
you could die on Monday.

06:11.319 --> 06:13.287
Who could be ready? Think about it.

06:13.288 --> 06:15.222
No, I'm trying not to think about it.

06:15.223 --> 06:16.289
I'm no good at denial.

06:16.290 --> 06:18.159
That's-that's why I drink!

06:18.160 --> 06:21.830
Well, she's supposed to avoid stress.

06:25.901 --> 06:27.869
We have to be the strong ones.

06:28.836 --> 06:30.638
Yeah.

06:30.838 --> 06:32.773
I can be strong.

06:34.943 --> 06:36.042
- Hey.
- Hi, guys.

06:36.043 --> 06:37.845
Hi.

06:38.313 --> 06:39.379
Oh, darling, I'm sorry I'm late,

06:39.380 --> 06:41.314
just finalizing this
massive project at work.

06:41.315 --> 06:44.084
Okay, Mum, you sit down,
I can-I can take this.

06:47.788 --> 06:48.989
Do you want a pillow?

06:48.990 --> 06:50.323
Stop fussing.

06:50.324 --> 06:52.994
I don't actually think I'm going to die.

06:54.930 --> 06:56.996
Well, I'll-I'll-I'll-I'll get
you a pillow for your feet.

06:56.997 --> 06:58.398
- I don't want any.
- I'll get two pillows.

06:58.399 --> 06:59.999
- Want any pillows.
- Three pillows.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.670
And then if you change your mind...

07:03.105 --> 07:05.004
The doctor said
it was a possibility.

07:05.005 --> 07:06.941
