12:36.303 --> 12:37.437
I'm not leaving.

12:37.438 --> 12:38.439
Never again, never.

12:38.440 --> 12:40.273
Grace, are you speaking?

12:40.274 --> 12:42.410
Uh huh.

12:44.078 --> 12:45.678
Richard.

12:45.679 --> 12:48.348
- Hi.
- Yeah, hi, Tom.

12:49.417 --> 12:50.817
Wow.

12:50.818 --> 12:53.487
Uh, I heard voices, but uh-

12:53.687 --> 12:55.857
well, I didn't expect to see you.

12:56.356 --> 12:58.224
Really, Tom? Really?

12:58.225 --> 12:59.359
Yeah, yeah.

12:59.360 --> 13:01.161
Really, yeah.

13:01.830 --> 13:03.162
Congratulations on the new novel.

13:03.163 --> 13:05.165
I haven't had a chance to read it yet,

13:05.166 --> 13:06.834
<i>but they said on the
radio you might win</i>

13:06.835 --> 13:08.569
a second Tolstoy Prize.

13:08.570 --> 13:10.737
Why on earth would I want
to talk about my book.

13:10.738 --> 13:12.540
