Brooke had the kind of beauty-

15:13.695 --> 15:14.760
Yeah, he's leaving.

15:14.761 --> 15:17.264
Of course, he's leaving.

15:19.333 --> 15:21.301
So, what's for breakfast?

15:22.236 --> 15:23.570
"This is very kind
of you," said Dorothea,

15:23.571 --> 15:25.305
<i>looking up at Mr.
Casaubon with delight.</i>

15:25.306 --> 15:26.505
"It is noble. After all,

15:26.506 --> 15:27.840
people may have some vocation"-

15:27.841 --> 15:29.375
You made him breakfast in bed?

15:29.376 --> 15:31.311
You never made me breakfast in bed.

15:31.312 --> 15:32.378
It's for Zoe.

15:32.379 --> 15:33.379
Oh, yeah.

15:33.380 --> 15:35.182
Yeah, okay.

15:35.350 --> 15:36.849
Carry on.

15:36.850 --> 15:38.652
You're still here?

15:41.755 --> 15:44.425
Thought you would've gone by now.

15:47.794 --> 15:49.596
Oh, Mum.

15:54.802 --> 15:56.369
Everything's gonna be okay.

15:56.370 --> 15:57.903
No, that's not what Kaitlyn said.

15:57.904 --> 15:59.873
I'm sure they can
cut the whole thing out.

15:59.874 --> 16:01.608
I need to have a little bit of radiation.

16:01.609 --> 16:03.578
It'll be fine.

16:03.979 --> 16:06.412
I'm just sorry that you had
to leave your great new job

16:06.413 --> 16:07.748
in London and come home.

16:07.749 --> 16:09.416
<i>I've got to go to work because</i>

16:09.417 --> 16:11.350
<i>the model has arrived
for the new project.</i>

16:11.351 --> 16:12.652
You're going to work?

16:12.653 --> 16:13.920
Yeah.

16:13.921 --> 16:15.388
Which goes to show what a little fuss

16:15.389 --> 16:16.757
about nothing this all is.

16:16.758 --> 16:17.791
Okay.

16:17.792 --> 16:19.593
<i>Go back to sleep.</i>

16:22.663 --> 16:23.930
Oh, Mum.

16:23.931 --> 16:25.065
I brought dad with me.

16:25.066 --> 16:27.033
Is that okay?

16:27.034 --> 16:29.036
Yeah.

16:29.037 --> 16:30.838
The more, the merrier.

16:33.908 --> 16:35.709
Hey.

16:39.514 --> 16:40.781
Right.

16:40.782 --> 16:41.947
I'm off.

16:41.948 --> 16:43.517
You're going to work?

16:43.518 --> 16:44.950
Of course, I am.

16:44.951 --> 16:46.787
I'm not the jerk who makes
loads of money writing

16:46.788 --> 16:48.788
pretentious, self-serving lies about

16:48.789 --> 16:50.923
someone I used to be married to.

16:50.924 --> 16:51.925
Speaking of which,

16:51.926 --> 16:53.960
I expect you to be gone
by the time I get home.

16:53.961 --> 16:55.329
I have only written about our marriage

16:55.330 --> 16:56.397
in my first novel.

16:56.398 --> 16:58.398
Which won one of the
biggest prizes in the world.

16:58.399 --> 17:00.801
<i>It's still in print,
a modern classic.</i>

17:00.802 --> 17:02.101
They teach it in schools.

17:02.102 --> 17:03.237
But nobody knew that was based on you.

17:03.238 --> 17:07.074
The fragile but brilliant
hero's neurotic first wife

17:07.075 --> 17:08.075
<i>named Kelly?</i>

17:08.076 --> 17:09.575
<i>As in Grace Kelly?</i>

17:09.576 --> 17:11.077
Everybody knew!

17:11.078 --> 17:13.412
I don't have time for this in so many ways.

17:13.413 --> 17:14.413
Richard, please,

17:14.414 --> 17:16.115
let this be our final goodbye.

17:16.116 --> 17:20.119
The man who makes dying
feel like an easier option.

17:28.363 --> 17:29.595
<i>You're not really going to work?</i>

17:29.596 --> 17:30.831
<i>I am going to work.</i>

17:30.832 --> 17:32.833
<i>Nah, you've got a secret life.</i>

17:32.834 --> 17:35.636
- A rendezvous with a lover.
- I've got a meeting at 10.

17:35.836 --> 17:37.104
<i>Jesus.</i>

17:37.105 --> 17:38.471
<i>Is this really who you've become?</i>

17:38.472 --> 17:39.873
The kind of person that goes to the office

17:39.874 --> 17:41.107
when they're dying?

17:41.108 --> 17:43.143
I don't actually think I am dying.

17:43.144 --> 17:44.745
Yeah, you know what, you may be,

17:44.746 --> 17:46.479
and on Monday.

17:46.480 --> 17:49.449
And, just look at you.

17:49.450 --> 17:50.584
<i>What? I-</i>

17:50.585 --> 17:51.852
I like my suit.

17:51.853 --> 17:54.655
<i>I'm not talking about your suit.</i>

17:55.623 --> 17:56.856
You're not afraid! Why not?

17:56.857 --> 17:58.458
Don't tell me how I feel.

17:58.459 --> 18:00.025
I always know how you feel.

18:01.028 --> 18:03.063
The great genius at work.

18:03.064 --> 18:05.664
How am I feeling now, Richard?

18:05.665 --> 18:06.799
Do the words,

18:06.800 --> 18:09.001
fuck you, come to mind?

18:09.002 --> 18:10.804
And not in a good way.

18:10.805 --> 18:11.604
You know, you're right.

18:11.605 --> 18:13.073
We should've just done it then.

18:13.074 --> 18:14.141
Done what?

18:14.142 --> 18:16.144
This.

18:18.145 --> 18:20.680
<i>What are you doing?</i>

18:22.016 --> 18:23.617
Do you remember

18:23.651 --> 18:25.085
when our marriage was falling apart,

18:25.086 --> 18:26.819
we were walking down
some street in Islington,

18:26.820 --> 18:29.489
and you started crying?

18:29.490 --> 18:31.825
<i>And you said that you didn't
want to be one of those</i>

18:31.826 --> 18:33.960
<i>little people who gets
married and divorced,</i>

18:33.961 --> 18:34.960
and married and divorced,

18:34.961 --> 18:36.095
you wanted to be a big person

18:36.096 --> 18:37.897
with one great love,

18:37.898 --> 18:39.466
and if we were gonna be

18:39.467 --> 18:41.902
<i>petty little people
with little lives then</i>

18:41.903 --> 18:43.836
why don't we just lie down
in the middle of the road

18:43.837 --> 18:45.905
until some kind bugger ran over us and

18:45.906 --> 18:47.173
put us out of our misery?

18:47.174 --> 18:48.842
Did I ever really think
love was that important?

18:48.843 --> 18:50.576
God, I was so young.

18:50.577 --> 18:51.978
Love is that important.

18:51.979 --> 18:53.447
Get up!

18:53.448 --> 18:54.248
<i>Don't do this!</i>

18:54.249 --> 18:55.316
I've only got four days to live,

18:55.317 --> 18:58.452
and I don't have time to
save your worthless life.

18:59.186 --> 19:01.188
Everything okay?

19:01.788 --> 19:03.589
Yeah, yeah, it's fine.

19:03.590 --> 19:05.659
Finish your breakfast.

19:05.660 --> 19:07.460
I heard yelling.

19:07.461 --> 19:09.363
Yeah, sure.

19:09.663 --> 19:11.064
I'll see you tonight.

19:11.065 --> 19:13.201
<i>Yeah, okay.</i>

19:14.201 --> 19:16.337
I love you.

19:16.737 --> 19:18.539
Oh, Grace?

19:19.073 --> 19:21.742
Do we have any of those muffins?

19:22.143 --> 19:24.978
Yeah, I-I think we got
one left in the fridge.

19:24.979 --> 19:27.248
<i>Okay, thanks.</i>

19:28.950 --> 19:30.885
And you still love me.

19:33.086 --> 19:34.086
So,

19:34.087 --> 19:36.389
how long in the microwave?

19:36.824 --> 19:38.091
Uh,

19:38.092 --> 19:39.692
just about 30 seconds.

19:39.693 --> 19:42.495
Yeah, yeah, thank you.

19:45.266 --> 19:46.600
Get run over,

19:46.601 --> 19:47.700
I'm going to work.

19:47.701 --> 19:48.969
How can you go to work?

19:48.970 --> 19:50.237
<i>'Cause it's a big project for me.</i>

19:50.238 --> 19:51.570
<i>I spent ages on this.</i>

19:51.571 --> 19:52.572
And now I've missed my bus.

19:52.573 --> 19:55.741
I'm gonna be late for
my meeting, you bastard!

19:55.742 --> 19:57.110
I know why you're not afraid.

19:57.111 --> 19:59.246
You're not afraid because
you're already dead.

19:59.247 --> 20:01.714
<i>Well, I'm here to
bring you back to life!</i>

20:01.715 --> 20:05.518
Well, wouldn't that be cruel
under the circumstances?

20:14.595 --> 20:16.129
Okay.

20:16.130 --> 20:17.932
Let's do it.

20:19.599 --> 20:21.401
Tada!

20:21.736 --> 20:22.802
Wow.

20:22.803 --> 20:24.605
<i>There's the pond.</i>

20:24.872 --> 20:26.906
And the playground.

20:26.907 --> 20:30.877
No units smaller than 243 square feet.

20:31.811 --> 20:34.881
<i>This is the biggest project I've
ever been lead architect on,</i>

20:34.882 --> 20:36.883
and so much work has gone into it and

20:36.884 --> 20:39.854
<i>we really gave it our all.</i>

20:40.153 --> 20:42.689
Just look at it.

20:42.690 --> 20:45.825
<i>The little cars and</i>

20:45.826 --> 20:48.328
the little people.

20:50.163 --> 20:52.832
Months of work.

20:55.670 --> 20:57.571
And it's...

20:58.306 --> 21:00.641
it-it...

21:02.309 --> 21:04.010
It's shit.

21:19.660 --> 21:20.794
Hey.

21:20.795 --> 21:21.795
You okay?

21:21.796 --> 21:22.796
Yeah.

21:22.797 --> 21:23.829
Yeah, no, I'm fine.

21:23.830 --> 21:25.664
'Cause you-you seem kind of,

21:25.665 --> 21:26.665
um, you know, different.

21:26.666 --> 21:28.735
No, no, no, same old Grace.

21:28.736 --> 21:30.002
You know, if anything's happening,

21:30.003 --> 21:31.337
you can tell me, right?

21:31.338 --> 21:33.473
'Cause I'm your friend.

21:33.807 --> 21:35.374
Well...

21:35.375 --> 21:37.377
I knew it.

21:37.678 --> 21:39.480
Okay.

21:40.681 --> 21:41.981
Tell me everything.

21:41.982 --> 21:45.785
I am a little bit
distracted, because I, uh...

21:47.288 --> 21:49.790
I've got...

21:51.959 --> 21:53.761
<i>I've got-I've got-</i>

21:56.230 --> 21:57.730
I've got a house guest.

21:57.731 --> 21:59.532
Oh.

22:00.734 --> 22:01.867
<i>Oh, you know what?</i>

22:01.868 --> 22:03.702
<i>That explains everything.</i>

22:03.703 --> 22:05.904
'Cause I had my in-laws
visiting last month,

22:05.905 --> 22:07.707
and I could not wait for that to end.

22:07.708 --> 22:10.043
<i>Okay, is that on Tom's
side of the family?</i>

22:10.044 --> 22:11.243
Uh, more mine.

22:11.244 --> 22:13.278
Right, but I thought your parents were gone

22:13.279 --> 22:14.713
and then you're an only child.

22:14.714 --> 22:18.017
Yeah, actually, it's my first husband.

22:18.249 --> 22:19.052
Oh, Richard Feekery.

22:19.053 --> 22:21.755
So, Richard Feekery is
in your house right now.

22:21.756 --> 22:23.856
I love his books.

22:23.857 --> 22:25.892
<i>Stolen Dreams is
magnificent, 'cause,</i>

22:25.893 --> 22:28.294
like, he just understands women

22:28.295 --> 22:30.396
<i>and those sex scenes, come on.</i>

22:30.397 --> 22:32.198
<i>You must have bonked your brains out</i>

22:32.199 --> 22:33.999
when you were married to him.

22:34.000 --> 22:35.735
Okay, if I were you,

22:35.736 --> 22:37.269
<i>I would sneak into his bed
in the middle of the night</i>

22:37.270 --> 22:39.172
<i>and have my way with him.</i>

22:39.173 --> 22:41.274
<i>'Cause you only live once, right?</i>

22:41.275 --> 22:42.875
Yeah.

22:42.876 --> 22:43.876
<i>'Cause I'm thinking about it,</i>

22:43.877 --> 22:45.144
I can't help it.

22:45.145 --> 22:46.145
Phew!

22:46.146 --> 22:47.146
Is it hot in here?

22:47.147 --> 22:49.449
It's hot, let's open a window.

22:49.950 --> 22:52.619
Thank you for letting me know.

22:59.426 --> 23:01.928
Yeah, her Tolstoy Prize winning ex

23:01.929 --> 23:04.598
is visiting from London.

23:05.098 --> 23:07.767
<i>Some girls don't know
how lucky they are.</i>

23:12.940 --> 23:14.473
So, last night I told her that

23:14.474 --> 23:17.177
my life is going great.

23:18.112 --> 23:19.345
Is it?

23:19.346 --> 23:20.814
Yes.

23:20.815 --> 23:22.781
And you should do the same because

23:22.782 --> 23:25.585
she can't die in peace if
she's worried that we're losers.

23:27.855 --> 23:28.721
So you agree?

23:28.722 --> 23:29.756
That we're not losers? I don't know.

23:29.757 --> 23:31.790
I think that it's a
little bit early to tell.

23:31.791 --> 23:33.460
We still have a lot of
life to live, look at-

23:33.461 --> 23:36.261
Do you agree that we should
help her die in peace?

23:36.262 --> 23:37.730
Of course I do.

23:37.731 --> 23:39.065
Then why did you tell your father?

23:39.066 --> 23:40.799
They were married.

23:40.800 --> 23:42.868
When they were very young.

23:42.869 --> 23:44.738
And then they were divorced.

23:44.739 --> 23:46.540
He's like

23:47.007 --> 23:48.475
the first guy you ever kissed
at some stupid birthday party

23:48.476 --> 23:49.808
in somebody's basement.

23:49.809 --> 23:51.877
<i>Like, who even remembers him?</i>

23:51.878 --> 23:54.547
Kenny Slitzer.

23:54.981 --> 23:56.082
He was wonderful.

23:56.083 --> 23:57.950
She's supposed to avoid stress.

23:57.951 --> 23:59.352
<i>He said that he wants to be there</i>

23:59.353 --> 24:01.521
at her bedside when it happens.

24:01.955 --> 24:04.022
That is the definition of inappropriate.

24:04.023 --> 24:06.826
He said that she's the love of his life.

24:07.027 --> 24:08.761
My dad is the love of her life,

24:08.762 --> 24:13.233
or she wouldn't have left
your dad for my dad, right?

24:13.968 --> 24:15.300
I guess.

24:15.301 --> 24:16.469
<i>And if someone is the
love of your life,</i>

24:16.470 --> 24:18.872
then by definition you are
the love of their life too.

24:18.873 --> 24:20.373
I don't know.

24:20.374 --> 24:23.042
Our soul-mates can't
have different soul-mates.

24:23.544 --> 24:25.245
Yeah.

24:25.246 --> 24:27.047
Yeah.

24:27.280 --> 24:28.981
Yeah, you're right because
then life would just

24:28.982 --> 24:30.783
be too sad.

24:31.251 --> 24:32.885
Girls.

24:32.886 --> 24:34.386
- Hi, Tom.
- Yeah, Dad?

24:34.387 --> 24:35.454
I've thought of something that'll make

24:35.455 --> 24:37.257
your mum really happy.

24:37.258 --> 24:38.991
I knew you would.

24:38.992 --> 24:40.793
Pizza!

24:42.930 --> 24:44.030
Oh, shit.

24:47.401 --> 24:50.002
"We are not afraid of
telling over and over again

24:50.003 --> 24:52.037
how a man comes to love a woman

24:52.038 --> 24:54.575
and be wedded to her...

24:55.409 --> 24:57.211
You're still here?

24:57.877 --> 24:59.746
Of course I'm still here.

25:00.013 --> 25:01.914
And suspiciously alone.

25:01.915 --> 25:03.182
Please don't tell me
you murdered my husband

25:03.183 --> 25:05.418
just to have a subject
for your next pot-boiler.

25:05.419 --> 25:07.420
Nah, they've gone to get pizza.

25:07.421 --> 25:08.755
But,

25:08.756 --> 25:10.390
I think it's
supposed to be like a big surprise.

25:10.391 --> 25:12.192
I love pizza.

25:14.060 --> 25:15.194
<i>Richard, let me say this gently.</i>

25:15.195 --> 25:17.864
Get the fuck out of my house.

25:19.032 --> 25:20.833
I've missed you so much.

25:21.035 --> 25:22.302
I never should have left you.

25:22.303 --> 25:24.103
You didn't leave me.

25:24.104 --> 25:25.905
I left you.

25:26.173 --> 25:27.306
Or at least I threw your
clothes out of the window

25:27.307 --> 25:28.508
and changed the locks.

25:28.509 --> 25:30.043
We could have worked things out.

25:30.044 --> 25:31.110
I don't think so.

25:31.111 --> 25:33.046
Things weren't quite the same

25:33.047 --> 25:34.447
after a drunk woman rang me to tell me

25:34.448 --> 25:35.547
she was fucking my husband,

25:35.548 --> 25:37.983
it just somehow took the
sparkle out of our marriage.

25:37.984 --> 25:40.286
I don't know why, it just did.

25:41.121 --> 25:42.488
I was an ass-hole.

25:42.489 --> 25:44.992
Finally we agree on something.

25:45.058 --> 25:47.927
But you should have waited
for me to stop being an ass-hole

25:47.928 --> 25:50.095
instead of getting
yourself knocked up by Tom.

25:50.096 --> 25:51.931
Tom saved my life.

25:51.932 --> 25:52.966
If you hadn't got pregnant,

25:52.967 --> 25:54.934
you never would have divorced me.

25:55.336 --> 25:57.370
Why do women always get pregnant
at such inopportune times,

25:57.371 --> 25:59.338
it should only happen
when the stars are aligned

25:59.339 --> 26:00.940
and true love is present,

26:00.941 --> 26:02.075
not

26:02.076 --> 26:03.075
when the condom breaks.

26:03.076 --> 26:05.011
Kaitlyn was not an accident.

26:05.412 --> 26:07.145
Okay, well, yes, she was.

26:07.146 --> 26:09.348
She was the best accident
that ever happened to me.

26:09.349 --> 26:10.650
You never regret children,

26:10.651 --> 26:11.950
you only regret the men

26:11.951 --> 26:13.085
that fathered them.

26:13.086 --> 26:14.953
You only slept with him for revenge.

26:14.954 --> 26:17.257
Loneliness, lust, revenge,

26:17.258 --> 26:19.059
rank them.

26:19.626 --> 26:21.361
Anyway.

26:21.362 --> 26:22.961
It was so long ago and,

26:22.962 --> 26:25.397
and now I'm happily married and dying.

26:25.398 --> 26:27.366
Not the best time to start dating your ex.

26:27.367 --> 26:28.902
And then you moved here

26:28.903 --> 26:30.103
because you still loved me

26:30.104 --> 26:31.437
and you didn't want to be tempted.

26:31.438 --> 26:33.105
<i>I did not move to
Toronto because of you.</i>

26:33.106 --> 26:34.106
Oh yes, you did.

26:34.107 --> 26:35.107
I did not.

26:35.108 --> 26:36.909
But now I'm here

26:37.144 --> 26:38.945
and

26:39.546 --> 26:41.915
I love you, too.

26:42.415 --> 26:44.917
You don't know what love is.

26:44.984 --> 26:47.452
<i>It requires to occasionally
think about someone else.</i>

26:47.453 --> 26:48.287
You only think about

26:48.288 --> 26:51.125
the ever fascinating Richard Feekery.

26:52.058 --> 26:53.058
Tom is a real person.

26:53.059 --> 26:54.693
Tom knows what love is.

26:54.694 --> 26:56.863
I know what love is.

26:57.064 --> 26:58.932
Pizza time!

27:07.674 --> 27:09.142
You know, this wine you bought, Richard,

27:09.143 --> 27:11.811
it goes really well with pizza.

27:13.146 --> 27:16.348
It's a Chablis Grand Crus, 1987.

27:16.349 --> 27:18.351
Yeah? Is it? Well,

27:18.551 --> 27:20.018
I think I'll just

27:20.019 --> 27:21.821
have a little drop more.

27:29.063 --> 27:30.063
Oh, come on, everyone,

27:30.064 --> 27:31.431
stop looking so depressed.

27:31.432 --> 27:32.699
<i>There's no reason to give up hope.</i>

27:32.700 --> 27:34.433
I believe in miracles.

27:34.434 --> 27:36.302
<i>And-and doctors can be wrong.</i>

27:36.303 --> 27:38.104
Do you know 40% of hospital stays

27:38.105 --> 27:40.373
have at least one incident
of medical malpractice?

27:40.374 --> 27:41.740
That's true.

27:41.741 --> 27:43.075
That's very reassuring.

27:43.076 --> 27:44.177
Thank you.

27:44.178 --> 27:46.345
Yeah, it's not what the doctor said.

27:46.346 --> 27:48.381
It's-I just have a bad feeling about this.

27:48.382 --> 27:50.184
<i>And you know,</i>

27:50.317 --> 27:52.118
I'm a little psychic.

27:53.053 --> 27:55.320
Remember, I had that dream about the dog,

27:55.321 --> 27:56.588
and then the following week,

27:56.589 --> 27:58.591
the next door neighbour's dog

27:58.592 --> 28:00.192
was run over by a police car.

28:00.193 --> 28:02.194
<i>And then last summer, I kept saying,</i>

28:02.195 --> 28:03.261
something bad is gonna happen,

28:03.262 --> 28:04.329
something bad's gonna happen,

28:04.330 --> 28:08.067
and-and then they had that
earthquake in Argentina.

28:08.634 --> 28:10.068
Darling, it's so nice to see you.

28:10.069 --> 28:12.104
I want a blow-by-blow
account of your new job.

28:12.105 --> 28:13.139
